Job Purpose: The principal function of a Business Analyst includes gathering, analyzing, documenting and implementing project requirements.

Key Responsibilities and Accountabilities:

  Establish a satisfactory on-going business relationship with clients
  Adhere to timeline and deliverables set by Project Manager for each project
  To gather project/ specific module requirements for a project
  Analyze and provide feedback to client on feasibility of requirements
  To write detailed Functional Specifications to document client requirements and get sign off on Functional Specifications
  To convey clients’ requirements to developers clearly
  Manage a group of developers in timeline and resource commitment to deliverables
  Prepare project/specific module status report on a weekly and monthly basis to Project Manager
  Test sample data-sets to check that output from the program works as intended
  Conduct UAT with clients and record UAT results sign off
  Ensure requirement is implemented in Production
  Understand System implementation on main functions available
  Prepare training material and conduct client training on project/specific modules, as necessary

Key requirements:

  Degree in Business or Computing or related discipline with an emphasis in information systems
  At Least 3 years of working experience in the related field is a must and project management skills, a plus
  Self-driven individual and able to work in a matrix organization
  Creative and possess strong analytical and product management skills, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements
  Attention to details, tenacity and patience and able to work under pressure
  Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group, executives, managers, and subject matter experts
  Focus on team KPI
